$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Ka taea e koe te whakamahi hexadecimal hei huri i waenga i nga uara ira me te uara-rua. Hei tauira, ko te huri i te 10011011001010 ki te hautekauono ka puta ko te 0x4F. Ko te tikanga ko te uara 4F e tohu ana i te nama rua 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'I roto i te pangarau me te pūtaiao rorohiko, hexadecimal (ano hoki te turanga 16, hex ranei) he punaha tau tuunga me te radix, te turanga ranei, o te 16. Ka whakamahia e ia nga tohu motuhake tekau ma ono, ko te nuinga ko nga tohu 0–9 hei tohu i nga uara kore ki te iwa. me A, B, C, D, E, F (he rereke ranei a–f) hei tohu i nga uara tekau ki te tekau ma rima. Hei tauira, he rite te tau hautekauono 2AF3, i roto i te ira, ki te (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160), he 10,995 ranei.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Ko ia mati hexadecimal e tohu ana i nga mati-rua-rua (nga moka) (e kiia ana ko te &quot;nibble&quot;), a ko te whakamahinga tuatahi o te tohu hautekauono he ahua hoa-tangata mo nga uara tohu-rua i roto i te rorohiko me te hikohiko matihiko. Hei tauira, ka taea e nga uara paita te awhe mai i te 0 ki te 255 (te hautekau) engari he pai ake te whakaatu mai i nga mati hexadecimal e rua i te awhe 00 ki te FF. Hexadecimal hoki e whakamahia ana hei tohu i nga wahitau mahara rorohiko.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Ko te Hex he whakapotonga o te Hexadecimal, he mea hanga i runga i te turanga -16 te hanganga ka whakamahia hei whakamaarama me pehea te whakaatu i nga tohutohu ki nga rorohiko. I whakawhanakehia tenei punaha nama tohu 16 hei aukati i te tau-rua moka-8, na reira ka taea te whakawaehere i nga raraunga ki roto i nga rorohiko ngawari. Ka taea te tā me te pato ma te whakamahi i nga mati hex rereke e rua me ia mati hex e whakaatu ana i te nibble, te whakatakotoranga 4-bits ranei.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Ka whakamahia e tenei punaha tau nga tohu 16 e whakaatuhia ana i roto i te awhe mai i te 0-9, te AF ranei. Ko te 0–9 e tohu ana i nga tau tae atu ki te iwa ko te AF e tohuhia ana e te tau 10–15. Ina whakatauritea ki era atu momo punaha tau e toru, ka kiia ko te punaha tau hexadecimal te mea tino whai hua.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'He muhu to waehere hexadecimal';
